I think that the best solution will be to replace your layout with [ConstraintLayout](https://developer.android.com/training/constraint-layout)

**Let me explain:**

You know that your textSize is `54dp`, but this is a fixed size and using it on your view will make your screen to be not responsive (this is because different phones got different screen size, and  `54dp` may look really small on large phones)

Sure, you can create one layout for every screen size but with `ConstraintLayout` you can create one responsive layout.

---


For your layout you can use **those attributes:**

- `app:layout_constraintWidth_percent`

- `app:layout_constraintHeight_percent`

To manage the size of your views in percents relatively to the screen size.

**For example, this layout:**

    &lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;utf-8&quot;?&gt;
    &lt;android.support.constraint.ConstraintLayout 
      xmlns:android=&quot;http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android&quot;
      xmlns:app=&quot;http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto&quot;
      android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;
      android:layout_height=&quot;match_parent&quot;&gt;
  
    &lt;ImageView
        android:id=&quot;@+id/img&quot;
        android:layout_width=&quot;0dp&quot;
        android:layout_height=&quot;0dp&quot;
        android:scaleType=&quot;centerCrop&quot;
        android:src=&quot;@drawable/rose&quot;
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf=&quot;@+id/text&quot;
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf=&quot;parent&quot;
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf=&quot;parent&quot;
        app:layout_constraintTop_toTopOf=&quot;parent&quot; /&gt;

    &lt;TextView
        android:id=&quot;@+id/text&quot;
        android:layout_width=&quot;0dp&quot;
        android:layout_height=&quot;0dp&quot;
        app:layout_constraintHeight_percent=&quot;.15&quot;
        android:gravity=&quot;center&quot;
        android:ellipsize=&quot;end&quot;
        android:maxLines=&quot;3&quot;
        android:text=&quot;In May 2019, Italian broadcaster RAI announced that it had begun planning the 2020 edition of the Sanremo Music Festival. It was not confirmed whether the festival would be used to select Italy&#39;s participant for 2020.&quot;
        android:textColor=&quot;#000000&quot;
        android:textSize=&quot;16dp&quot;
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toBottomOf=&quot;parent&quot;
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf=&quot;parent&quot;
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf=&quot;parent&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/android.support.constraint.ConstraintLayout&gt;

In the above layout, your textView height is equal to 15% of the screen in height.
Your textView and the image will keep this ratio for every screen size given.

**And the layout will look like this:**

[![enter image description here][1]][1]


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/78dN1.png

Extra information:
-

Now after you have the picture of your layout you must be wondering to yourself &quot;why is my text being cut off, didn&#39;t he just mentioned how the layout is responsive?&quot;

I did mentioned it, if you want your text to fit the screen as well you can use [Autosizing TextViews](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/ui/look-and-feel/autosizing-textview)

